urfaceType":110},[],[218,219,220,221,222,223],"Gualtherus, 1624 [1625], Siciliæ obiacentium insular. et Bruttiorum antiquæ tabulæ, cum animadversionib","Kaibel, 1890, IG","Supplementum epigraphicum graecum, 1923-","Boeckh, Franz, 1853, CIG","Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano","Amata, 2016, Ricerche epigrafiche sul culto demetriaco in Sicilia",[225,226,227,228,229,230],"ZP8DE8KS","Q2SBPG9F","F2GG87EQ","TQMVHEVL","RZSFKACR","QUSE9NVG",[232,233,234,30,35,39,235,236,237,238,102,239,116],"isic001275","i.sicily inscription 001275",{"_":5},"catina","catania","sicilia","sicily","ancient greek",[],{"title":242,"body":243,"divs":244,"editions":269,"images":279,"handnote":285},"ISic001275. I.Sicily inscription 001275","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Giorgia Capra, Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Περσεφόνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Περσεφόνη\">Περσεφόνη\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>βασιλὶς \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Κατανα[ίων] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Giorgia Capra, Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Περσεφόνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Περσεφόνη\">ΠΕΡΣΕΦΟΝΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΒΑΣΙΛΙΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΚΑΤΑΝΑ[...]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001275_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001275_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001275.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001275-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of CIG (Franz)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΚΑΤΑΝΑ Λ; Manganaro: κατ'[ὄ]να[ρ]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\" https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1030-5679\">Giorgia Capra\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Persephone, queen of the Catanians\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The text is lost, but recorded by Gualtherus as being on the base of a clay statue one cubit high. There is much debate in the scholarship post-Gualtherus over whether the text and statue was a forgery or genuine. Kaibel and Franz both note that the existence of such a statue, and the accompanying text, at such an early date (pre-1624) is against the idea of a forgery. On the text of line 3, Gualtherus' presentation, is entirely compatible with the proposed reading of Franz and others, of a damaged final line (a gap for the iota, the lambda-like trace being the upper part of a rhomboid omega, and a lacuna following). The only basis for dating would be the limited evidence for letterforms, with rhomboid letters attested on the island from later C2 BCE onwards.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 38.0942 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 48 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5649f \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">450\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1988 68 n.346 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Amata 2016 104 \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Gualtherus reports rhomboid omicron alongside standard four-bar sigma and quadrate epsilon\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[245,248,251,254,257,260,263,266],{"id":246,"html":247},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Giorgia Capra, Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Περσεφόνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Περσεφόνη\">Περσεφόνη\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>βασιλὶς \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Κατανα[ίων] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Giorgia Capra, Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Περσεφόνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Περσεφόνη\">ΠΕΡΣΕΦΟΝΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΒΑΣΙΛΙΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΚΑΤΑΝΑ[...]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":249,"html":250},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001275_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001275_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001275.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001275-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":252,"html":253},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of CIG (Franz)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΚΑΤΑΝΑ Λ; Manganaro: κατ'[ὄ]να[ρ]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":255,"html":256},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\" https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1030-5679\">Giorgia Capra\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Persephone, queen of the Catanians\u003C/p>  ",{"id":258,"html":259},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The text is lost, but recorded by Gualtherus as being on the base of a clay statue one cubit high. There is much debate in the scholarship post-Gualtherus over whether the text and statue was a forgery or genuine. Kaibel and Franz both note that the existence of such a statue, and the accompanying text, at such an early date (pre-1624) is against the idea of a forgery. On the text of line 3, Gualtherus' presentation, is entirely compatible with the proposed reading of Franz and others, of a damaged final line (a gap for the iota, the lambda-like trace being the upper part of a rhomboid omega, and a lacuna following). The only basis for dating would be the limited evidence for letterforms, with rhomboid letters attested on the island from later C2 BCE onwards.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":261,"html":262},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 38.0942 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 48 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5649f \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">450\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1988 68 n.346 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Amata 2016 104 \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":264,"html":265},"handnote","\u003Cp>Gualtherus reports rhomboid omicron alongside standard four-bar sigma and quadrate epsilon\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":267,"html":268},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[270,272,275,276],{"html":271},"Text encoding: Giorgia Capra, Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\u003C/a>",{"id":273,"lang":116,"html":274},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Περσεφόνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Περσεφόνη\">Περσεφόνη\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cb